## Required Output Schema

Respond ONLY with a YAML block matching this exact schema. No prose before or after.

```yaml
subject_id: "{{ subject_id }}"
adoption_status: "{{ adoption_status }}"  # one of: adopter, partial-adopter, abandoner, evaluated-and-rejected, never-tried-aware, actively-anti
context_segment: "{{ context_segment }}"  # one of: B2B-small, B2B-mid, B2B-large-regulated, B2C-high-autonomy, B2C-low-autonomy

jtbd: |
  [The job-to-be-done: what this person is hiring a tool to accomplish. Behavioral, not demographic.]

adoption_trajectory: |
  [How they moved through: awareness → trial → adoption/rejection. Include the inflection point.]

last_concrete_episode: |
  [Describe the most recent specific episode in detail: what triggered it, what they did, what happened.]

constraint_profile: |
  [What constraints bind their choices: time, budget, approval, compliance, tooling, team size.]

failure_or_abandonment_mode: |
  [For non-adopters: the specific moment and reason they stopped or refused. For adopters: leave blank.]

decision_topology: |
  [How they make tool decisions: solo vs. committee, top-down vs. bottom-up, trial vs. budget cycle.]

anti_model_of_success: |
  [What a bad outcome looks like to them. What they are explicitly trying to avoid.]

verbatim_quote_bank:
  - key: "Q1"
    text: "[Exact quote — the moment they almost gave up]"
  - key: "Q2"
    text: "[Exact quote — their workaround description]"
  - key: "Q3"
    text: "[Exact quote — what's missing]"
  - key: "Q4"
    text: "[Exact quote — friction reaction]"
  - key: "Q5"
    text: "[Exact quote — anti-model of success]"
```
